- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-af6f8e89
  source:
    span_id: AI in health - WHO_removed/5-provision-with-general-purpose-foundation-models-lmms/5-2-measures-that-governments-can-introduce-to-address-such-/sent_0001
    citation: 5-provision-with-general-purpose-foundation-models-lmms/5-2-measures-that-governments-can-introduce-to-address-such-
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
  scope:
    data_domain:
    - health
    context:
    - internal
    actor:
    - developer
  hazard: harm from unsafe medical information
  conditions:
  - queries that request health or medical information
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Block queries that request health or medical information.
  - Attach a clear warning to any responses that include health or medical information.
  - Direct users to information or services that can provide appropriate assistance.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligations to block, warn, and refer are explicit and can be verified
      by inspecting model I/O and configuration.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-02b5cb25
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: 5-provision-with-general-purpose-foundation-models-lmms/5-2-measures-that-governments-can-introduce-to-address-such-
    span_id: AI in health - WHO_removed/5-provision-with-general-purpose-foundation-models-lmms/5-2-measures-that-governments-can-introduce-to-address-such-/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain:
    - health
    context: []
  hazard: harm from unsafe medical information
  conditions:
  - such measures are not taken
  - developer intends that users apply its LMM for health care, either directly or
    indirectly through a provider
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - If such measures are not taken or if the developer intends that users apply its
    LMM for health care, the developer shall assume and perform the specific responsibilities
    that only it can satisfy to address risks associated with use of the LMM in health
    care.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: 'Vague obligation: ''such measures'' and ''specific responsibilities''
      undefined, so no concrete observable predicate to check.'
    evidence_signals: []
